Command line
------------

Main parameter is -a :

-a field-spec[:func]

if not specified, func is rem

field-spec: n | n..m | ..m | n.. | field-spec,field-spec | !field-spec

where n and m are integers that can be > or < to 0 (but not =)

func : rem | avg | min | max | sum | first | last | smaller | greatest

sum, avg, min and max require numeric values (of any base, including ASCII, 
with '0' as the 0), while smaller and greater compare the values as string 
(ie. "1" is greated than "09").

